
New variable form for your Docker build & push pipeline authentication:

You need to create three secure variables in your Azure DevOps pipeline, because your YAML uses:

$(AZURE_CLIENT_ID)

$(AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET)

$(AZURE_TENANT_ID)

Step-by-step

Name → Variable name (exactly as in YAML):

AZURE_CLIENT_ID → value = the appId from your Service Principal

AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET → value = the password from your Service Principal

AZURE_TENANT_ID → value = the tenant from your Service Principal

Value → The actual sensitive value from the SPN creation output.

Check ✅ Keep this value secret for sensitive variables (CLIENT_SECRET especially).

Save the variable.

Example:

Name	Value	Keep secret?
AZURE_CLIENT_ID	xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx	❌ (can keep unsecret)
AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET	xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx	✅
AZURE_TENANT_ID	xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx	❌
